WEBVTT

00:15.320 --> 00:17.560
Autumn of the 24th year of Yuankang

00:18.120 --> 00:20.840
Prince of Jin Sikong Yao ascended the throne as emperor

00:21.040 --> 00:23.840
Posthumously honored late emperor Sikong Jing as Xuan Yuan Emperor

00:24.240 --> 00:26.320
Enfeoffed Sikong Sheng as crown prince

00:26.640 --> 00:29.400
Posthumously honored Lady Xie as Virtuous and Cultured Empress

00:29.680 --> 00:31.920
Enfeoffed Chen family's eldest daughter as consort

00:31.960 --> 00:33.400
Rank second to the empress

00:33.400 --> 00:35.400
Harmonious in the palace

00:56.440 --> 00:57.880
I, Sikong Yao

00:58.600 --> 01:00.640
Kneel and report to ancestors and heaven

01:01.800 --> 01:02.520
Since

01:02.880 --> 01:04.720
After the Jianping rebellion

01:05.080 --> 01:06.520
The Wuzhao invaded

01:06.520 --> 01:08.000
Disrupted our land

01:08.000 --> 01:10.040
I, being of Xuan's bloodline

01:10.400 --> 01:12.280
Should bear the ancestral state

01:12.400 --> 01:14.520
And care for the people

01:15.680 --> 01:17.800
Thus defeated Shilang at Yiyang

01:17.920 --> 01:19.840
Recovered the homeland in the north

01:20.120 --> 01:21.400
Old people

01:21.600 --> 01:23.080
All wept

01:23.360 --> 01:24.240
Saying

01:24.520 --> 01:27.520
Never thought to see the imperial army again today

01:27.720 --> 01:28.360
After

01:28.800 --> 01:30.120
The court bred traitors

01:30.960 --> 01:32.120
Acting perversely

01:32.680 --> 01:33.440
Yao

01:33.760 --> 01:35.000
Following ancestral teachings

01:35.280 --> 01:36.440
Raised troops in anger

01:36.520 --> 01:38.880
To seek state stability

01:39.160 --> 01:40.160
Now

01:40.600 --> 01:43.000
Above, for heaven and earth's will

01:43.240 --> 01:45.880
Below, for the people's support

01:46.640 --> 01:48.320
Set altar to worship heaven

01:48.400 --> 01:49.840
Announce to all under heaven

01:49.880 --> 01:51.600
Inherit the great succession

01:51.840 --> 01:53.080
Change era name

01:53.800 --> 01:55.400
Longwu

01:59.000 --> 02:01.880
Long live Your Majesty

02:17.400 --> 02:18.160
Reward

02:18.320 --> 02:19.600
Xie Jian'an

02:19.600 --> 02:21.000
Authority commands respect

02:21.040 --> 02:22.640
Merit surpasses all ministers

02:22.840 --> 02:24.120
Promote to Minister over the Masses

02:24.360 --> 02:26.080
Enfeoff as Duke of Qing

02:26.200 --> 02:27.400
Appoint as Chancellor

02:27.880 --> 02:29.600
Command Six Ministries and Nine Courts

02:29.840 --> 02:31.360
Record Secretariat affairs

02:31.560 --> 02:33.280
Govern Jingzhou

02:34.600 --> 02:35.520
Zu Yue

02:35.640 --> 02:37.000
Loyal and humble

02:37.000 --> 02:38.360
Brave and resolute

02:38.600 --> 02:40.560
Promote to General of Agile Cavalry

02:40.640 --> 02:42.120
Enfeoff as Marquis of Wuwu

02:42.200 --> 02:43.520
Govern Dingzhou

02:43.720 --> 02:46.000
Command all military affairs in the north

02:46.080 --> 02:47.160
Xie Xuan

02:47.160 --> 02:48.560
Outmaneuvers enemies

02:48.640 --> 02:50.000
Skilled in both civil and military

02:50.160 --> 02:51.840
Enfeoff as Marquis of Yongning

02:51.880 --> 02:53.400
Appoint as Secretariat Gentleman

02:53.440 --> 02:55.120
Concurrently Grand Tutor to the Crown Prince

02:55.240 --> 02:57.000
Hold rank of Grandee of the Palace

02:57.000 --> 02:58.840
Grant gold seal and purple ribbon

02:58.840 --> 03:00.000
Zhu Yuanzhi

03:00.120 --> 03:01.520
Steady and strategic

03:01.600 --> 03:03.040
Brave and decisive

03:03.160 --> 03:04.960
Enfeoff as General Who Guards the North

03:05.000 --> 03:06.200
Appoint as Grand Commandant

03:06.520 --> 03:09.680
Govern Qing, Yan, Ping, and Liang prefectures

03:09.680 --> 03:10.880
Strike first to gain advantage

03:10.920 --> 03:11.400
Posthumously honor

03:11.440 --> 03:13.400
Late Great General Zu Kun

03:13.520 --> 03:15.520
As Loyal and Martial Guardian Duke

03:15.640 --> 03:17.120
To be enshrined in the ancestral temple

03:17.200 --> 03:18.880
Build temple and establish worship

03:19.000 --> 03:19.520
Posthumously honor

03:19.520 --> 03:21.760
Late Colonel Director of Retainers Chu Huan

03:21.760 --> 03:23.280
As Marquis of Dingxiang

03:23.400 --> 03:24.640
His son Chu Meng

03:24.640 --> 03:26.400
Appoint as Colonel of the Feathered Forest

03:26.440 --> 03:28.240
Command capital guard

03:28.280 --> 03:29.800
Inherit title for three generations

03:30.160 --> 03:30.640
Posthumously honor

03:30.640 --> 03:33.200
Late Liu Dadao as Marquis of Wuyi

03:33.320 --> 03:35.840
Grant Liu Nian as Zhaoyi

03:35.840 --> 03:37.400
Enter the empress's quarters

03:37.560 --> 03:38.000
Posthumously honor

03:38.000 --> 03:41.680
Late Director of the Imperial Academy Yugong as Grand Preceptor

03:41.760 --> 03:44.880
His disciple Wang Ming promoted to Censor-in-Chief

03:45.720 --> 03:48.200
Qiu Sheng enfeoffed as Count of Yunxian

03:48.280 --> 03:49.680
Grant one thousand bolts of silk

03:49.680 --> 03:51.680
Command Beishuo Army as Major

03:51.760 --> 03:55.800
Qi Jiu and Lin Shu appointed as Left and Right Guard Colonels

03:56.000 --> 03:58.720
Each granted bright armor and ring-pommel sword

03:58.840 --> 04:00.160
Guard the palace

04:00.600 --> 04:03.440
Posthumously honor late Vice Minister of Revenue Cao Biaozhi

04:03.440 --> 04:05.360
As Marquis of Nanxiang, Cultured and Loyal

04:05.600 --> 04:06.680
Announce far and wide

04:06.720 --> 04:08.040
Let all know

04:08.040 --> 04:09.520
Let those in charge implement

04:09.680 --> 04:13.200
Jiazi day, October of the 24th year of Yuankang
